Aril runtime support code — license
====================================

The Aril *compiler* is licensed under the Apache License 2.0 (see LICENSE).

Separately, the Aril *runtime support code* — the code the Aril compiler emits
into the programs it compiles, i.e. this `arilrt` runtime package (whether
imported in vendored builds or inlined into a single file) — is licensed under
the BSD Zero Clause License (0BSD), reproduced below. This means programs you
compile with Aril carry no
Aril attribution or licensing obligation — mirroring how TypeScript's emitted
helpers (tslib) are 0BSD.

